title: NASA hits limits of space station utilization
summary: NASA has effectively reached full utilization of the International Space Station given limitations on crew time and the ability to get cargo to and from the station, an agency official said Jan. 30.

title: House passes commercial remote sensing bill
summary: The House Science Committee scored a bipartisan victory Jan. 30 with the passage of a minor commercial remote sensing bill even before the committee’s first meeting of the new Congress.

title: Lockheed Martin to launch first demo of new mid-size bus
summary: Lockheed Martin plans to launch the first demonstration mission of its new LM 400 mid-sized satellite bus in 2023.

title: Inmarsat-6 F2 satellite completes three-day trip to SpaceX launch site
summary: Inmarsat’s latest geostationary telecoms satellite has arrived at its Florida launch site after a three-day journey from Airbus’ testing facilities in France.

title: Former NASA Astronauts to Receive Congressional Space Medal of Honor
summary: Vice President Kamala Harris will award former NASA astronauts Douglas Hurley and Robert Behnken the Congressional Space Medal of Honor at 4:15 p.m. EST on Tuesday, Jan. 31. Hurley and Behnken will receive the award for bravery in NASA’s SpaceX Demonstration Mission-2 (Demo-2) to the International Space Station in 2020.
